This paper deals with knowledge graph completion, which is a common task in natural language processing and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a one-shot relational learning framework that utilizes embedding models and graph structures to predict new facts in knowledge graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new learning framework. The paper also deals with natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with knowledge graphs.
